text: B23 may refer to: * a human nucleolar protein also known as NPM1 * the 2.3L, pre-revision variant of the Volvo Redblock engine * Bundesstraße 23, federal highway in Germany * the data engineering and software development company, which created the B23 data platform, an artificial intelligence engine to discover, transform, and synthesize data from a variety of sources to provide unique and predictive insights. * B-23, national highway in Catalonia == Other uses == * B-23 Dragon, a 1930s bomber aircraft * B-23 (Michigan county highway)
title: B23
